{"id":55470,"title":"Genome-wide association studies of refractive error and myopia, lessons learned, and implications for the future.","abstract":"The investigation of the genetic basis of refractive error and myopia entered a new stage with the introduction of genome-wide association studies (GWAS). Multiple GWAS on many ethnic groups have been published over the years, providing new insight into the genetic architecture and pathophysiology of refractive error. This is a review of the GWAS published to date, the main lessons learned, and future possible directions of genetic studies of myopia and refractive error. ","date":"2014-05-30","categories":"Eye Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24876304","annotations":[{"name":"Ethnic group","weight":0.464836,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethnic_group"},{"name":"Genetics","weight":0.219465,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetics"},{"name":"Genetic association","weight":0.115795,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetic_association"},{"name":"Myopia","weight":0.0503012,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myopia"},{"name":"Architecture","weight":0.0377168,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Architecture"},{"name":"Refractive error","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Refractive_error"},{"name":"Pathophysiology","weight":0.0287296,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathophysiology"},{"name":"Genome-wide association study","weight":0.0262143,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genome-wide_association_study"},{"name":"Error (baseball)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Error_(baseball)"},{"name":"Stage (theatre)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stage_(theatre)"},{"name":"Refraction","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Refraction"},{"name":"Insight"